                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Hand a: mediocre but careful. (Texts I-III). The handwriting is characterized by a
                           rounded script with tendency to right-sloping
                           letters Hand b: poor.</seg>
                        <locus from="4ra" to="46vb">4ra-46vb</locus>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid scarlet: hand a, moderate amaranth: hand
                           b)</seg>
                        <date>First half of the 20th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names; name of the protagonist, his baptismal
                           name Krǝstos ʾAbuhu (e.g. fol. 9ra) and names of his parents Yǝrdǝʿannä
                           ʾƎgziʾ and Märkeza (e.g. fol. 6vb); names of other saints like Qirqos
                           (e.g. fol. 7ra), ʾAmanuʾel (e.g. fol. 9va), Gabra Nazrawi (e.g. fol.
                           12vb), Giyorgis (e.g. fol. 26vb); Mäṭaʿ (fol. 41rb), Libānos (fol. 41va);
                           names of the donors. 
 A few lines in the incipit page of Text I,
                           incipit of Texts II-V, incipits of the sections of all texts.
 A few
                           words like Manfas Qǝddus "Holy Spirit", ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer "God", Śǝllāse
                           "Trinity", Ṗarāqliṭos "Paraclete"; words sǝmʿu "listen!" (fol. 40rb) and
                           wa-halläwa "they existed" (fol. 41rb) and the word salām.
 Elements
                           of the punctuation signs and text dividers; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic"> 
                        <seg type="script">Hand b: poor. (Texts IV and V). The handwriting is crude and very
                           irregular</seg>
                        <locus from="48va" to="56va">48va-56va</locus>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid scarlet: hand a, moderate amaranth: hand
                           b)</seg>
                        <date>First half of the 20th century</date>
                        
                     
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">- <locus target="#4r">4r</locus> (incipit
                        page of Text I): recent, coloured (rose, orange, brown, black) ornamental
                        band; interlaces, floral and anthropomorphic motifs.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#46vb">f. 46vb</locus>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">Donation note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#46vb">46vb</locus>: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘደጃዝማች፡ ወልደ፡ ገብርኤል፡ ዘአቡሁ፡
                              ተክለ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወእሙ፡ ወለተ፡ አናንያ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ለታቦተ፡ አቡነ፡ ማማስ፡ ዘገርሕሴ፡ በዘመነ፡ ንጉሥነ፡
                              ኃይለ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወመስፍንነ፡ ልዑል፡ ራስ፡ ጉግሣ፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርሐ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ዘሠረቆ፡
                              ወዘፈሐቆ፡ ው[<locus target="#47ra">47ra</locus>]ጉዝ፡ ውእቱ፡ በአፈ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡
                              ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ወበአፈ፡ ፲ወ፪ ሐዋርያት። በ፲ወ፱፳ወ፬ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት...</q>
                           <note> The note states that daǧǧāzmāč Walda Gabrǝʾel
                           donated the book to the church of ʾAbuna Mamas of Gärhǝse in 1924 A.M. (=
                           1931/32 A.D.), in the time of King Ḫāyla Śǝllāse I (r. 1930-74) and lǝʿul
                              rās Gugsa ʾArʾaya (d. 1933, EAE II, 905-06). The note is
                              followed by an exhortation to the readers to pray for the donor. Two
                              stamps are beneath the note. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc> Short supplication for the scribe: <locus target="#56va">56va</locus>.
 - A few corrections written interlineally: e.g.,
                           <locus target="#45ra">45ra</locus>, 49ra.</desc>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><desc>Small crosses, near
                           to the rubricated words: fols 40r, 41r. </desc>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"><desc> Two illegible stamps:
                           <locus target="#47r">47r</locus>.</desc>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4"><desc>Many doodles (repetition of
                           text passages or names of saints) in the upper margin, in pen: e.g.,
                              <locus target="#6v">6v</locus>, 9r, 10r, 12v, 14v, 15r, 20r, 24v, 25v,
                           35v, 36r, 37r, 41r, 43r, 44r.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc type="findingAid"> Crude text dividers: fols. 29ra (incipit page of
                              Text II), 43rb (incipit page of Text III).</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
